manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Essential Vitamin A: Vitamin A is a fat-soluble antioxidant that can be stored in the body for a long time. But that's not all Vitamin A can do. It is often added to skin creams, ointments, and injectables. In this form, you will see it as retinol and it is used in many products, serums, powders, oils, liquids, gummies, capsules, pills, and other topical solutions for the face, like lotions. Retinal is another form of Vitamin A. Pure Vitamin A in Foods: There are many food sources that can be found in nature that contain Vitamin A for people that are seeking health from their diets. Orange foods, like sweet potatoes and carrots contain Vitamin A. Many meat sources are also rich in Vitamin A, including beef liver, lamb liver, salmon, butter, hard-boiled eggs, trout, fish liver oil, and cod. Vitamin A is also commonly found in multivitamins, gels, and chewables. If you do not get enough Vitamin A from your diet, our Vitamin A supplement can help! Nature's Truth Vitamin A (as Retinyl Palmitate): Nature's Truth Vitamin A offers a high potency formula that provides 10,000 IUs of this essential vitamin in convenient quick release softgels. Purity and potency are our top priorities at Nature's Truth, which is why our formula is Non-GMO, Gluten-Free and contains no Artificial Flavor, Sweetener or Preservatives.
